            <title>[MJAVADOC-93] Allow commas in text arguments doctitle, windowtitle, header, footer, and bottom [PATCH ATTACHED]</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-93</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Allow commas in text arguments doctitle, windowtitle, header, footer, and bottom. By default quiet every argument value for the javadoctool will be added comma-separated (each token one cmd-line-arg) and the comma itself will be of course omitted. But in arguments doctitle, windowtitle, header, footer, and bottom this should not be applied. The appended patch solves this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cheers,&lt;br/&gt;
Martin&lt;br/&gt;
